1
00:00:10,177 --> 00:00:12,567
What are you doing?

2
00:00:12,567 --> 00:00:14,567
Hold on.

3
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:17,069
[Manager]
Hey, it's from work. Take it.

4
00:00:20,634 --> 00:00:22,589
A merger?

5
00:00:24,601 --> 00:00:26,046
With Unicorn?

6
00:00:26,046 --> 00:00:28,161
If not, leave me alone.

7
00:00:29,634 --> 00:00:31,977
I don't want to see you ever again.

8
00:00:33,467 --> 00:00:35,068
Okay.

9
00:00:35,701 --> 00:00:37,528
If you want it that badly.

10
00:00:38,133 --> 00:00:40,232
Let's never cross paths again.

11
00:00:42,901 --> 00:00:44,111
That's right.

12
00:00:44,111 --> 00:00:45,761
You'd know, too.

13
00:00:45,761 --> 00:00:47,514
It's Soo An's agency.

14
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:54,096
Who saw this coming?

15
00:00:54,096 --> 00:00:56,534
Hyun Jae.

16
00:00:56,534 --> 00:00:57,567
Good to see you.

17
00:00:57,567 --> 00:00:59,293
Yeah. See you later.

18
00:00:59,293 --> 00:01:00,926
Take care.

19
00:01:01,868 --> 00:01:04,450
No point hiding now, right?

20
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:08,235
You never know.

21
00:01:08,235 --> 00:01:10,170
Why did you drag me here?

22
00:01:10,170 --> 00:01:11,280
I said I didn't want to come.

23
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:12,735
What do you mean?

24
00:01:12,735 --> 00:01:14,103
You got the call too.

25
00:01:14,103 --> 00:01:15,309
That's what I'm saying,

26
00:01:15,309 --> 00:01:17,234
why on earth?

27
00:01:17,234 --> 00:01:18,868
Hyun Jae!

28
00:01:18,868 --> 00:01:20,980
- Huh?
- Hyun Jae!

29
00:01:23,834 --> 00:01:25,667
Congrats on the comeback.

30
00:01:25,667 --> 00:01:27,671
Yeah. It's been a while.

31
00:01:27,671 --> 00:01:29,506
I watched everything you did,

32
00:01:29,506 --> 00:01:30,757
you were amazing.

33
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:31,968
I'm such a huge fan,

34
00:01:31,968 --> 00:01:33,827
could I get one picture?

35
00:01:33,827 --> 00:01:35,654
Sure.

36
00:01:43,467 --> 00:01:45,480
Thank you.

37
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:47,325
You're Jae Min, right?

38
00:01:47,325 --> 00:01:48,501
Hi.

39
00:01:48,501 --> 00:01:49,733
Oh,

40
00:01:49,733 --> 00:01:51,411
hey.

41
00:01:51,411 --> 00:01:52,965
Let's go.

42
00:01:56,153 --> 00:01:57,434
Didn't he quit?

43
00:01:57,434 --> 00:01:58,485
Who is he?

44
00:01:58,485 --> 00:02:00,100
Jae Min from Next Stage Survival.

45
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:02,622
- The stalker?
- Keep it down.

46
00:02:03,633 --> 00:02:06,734
That's what I want to know.

47
00:02:06,734 --> 00:02:08,542
- Come on.
- Okay.

48
00:02:08,542 --> 00:02:10,425
[PNJS Entertainment]

49
00:02:15,369 --> 00:02:17,537
Those guys are from Unicorn.

50
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,507
If we train here,

51
00:02:20,507 --> 00:02:22,447
it's going to get wild.

52
00:02:30,701 --> 00:02:31,818
Soo An!

53
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:33,392
Hey.

54
00:02:55,217 --> 00:02:58,945
You've all seen the news,

55
00:02:58,945 --> 00:03:02,015
PNJS has merged with Unicorn,

56
00:03:02,015 --> 00:03:05,223
so their trainees are joining us.

57
00:03:05,223 --> 00:03:07,145
You'll share practice rooms,

58
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:08,981
and take evaluations together,

59
00:03:08,981 --> 00:03:11,275
so introduce yourselves and get along.

60
00:03:11,275 --> 00:03:12,985
- Yes.
- Yes.

61
00:03:12,985 --> 00:03:14,267
And here's the key part,

62
00:03:14,267 --> 00:03:15,629
the ten of you in this room

63
00:03:15,629 --> 00:03:20,267
are candidates for the boy group
debuting later this year.

64
00:03:20,267 --> 00:03:21,868
There's a test coming soon,

65
00:03:21,868 --> 00:03:24,329
so keep that in mind.

66
00:03:24,329 --> 00:03:26,567
Good luck with practice!

67
00:03:26,567 --> 00:03:28,574
Yes, it's me.

68
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:36,185
A test already?

69
00:03:36,185 --> 00:03:37,843
Isn't this unfair to us?

70
00:03:37,843 --> 00:03:40,634
This is corporate bullying.

71
00:03:40,634 --> 00:03:42,244
They're not even that big.

72
00:03:42,244 --> 00:03:43,307
Hey.

73
00:03:43,307 --> 00:03:45,434
The bigger fish eats the smaller one.

74
00:03:45,434 --> 00:03:47,093
Fair point.

75
00:03:49,104 --> 00:03:50,625
I can't believe I'm debuting with you.

76
00:03:50,625 --> 00:03:52,418
I know, right?

77
00:03:52,418 --> 00:03:53,700
I have to test too.

78
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:56,567
You're already locked in.

79
00:03:56,567 --> 00:03:57,737
But still,

80
00:03:57,737 --> 00:04:01,106
we test alongside them, right?

81
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:04,208
It's always been competitive,

82
00:04:04,208 --> 00:04:07,033
now it'll be worse.

83
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:09,149
- I'm jealous.
- Of what?

84
00:04:09,149 --> 00:04:10,584
You'll debut.

85
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:12,352
What are you saying?

86
00:04:12,352 --> 00:04:13,713
Seriously,

87
00:04:13,713 --> 00:04:14,955
with the right agency,

88
00:04:14,955 --> 00:04:17,174
you'd have debuted ages ago.

89
00:04:17,174 --> 00:04:19,993
If our ace doesn't debut, who will?

90
00:04:19,993 --> 00:04:21,334
Exactly.

91
00:04:21,334 --> 00:04:23,734
What? We can all debut together.

92
00:04:23,734 --> 00:04:26,308
No, you have to debut
for us to feel good about ourselves.

93
00:04:26,308 --> 00:04:28,727
Right, you're the best.

94
00:04:28,727 --> 00:04:29,853
You little punk.

95
00:04:29,853 --> 00:04:32,334
The best!

96
00:04:32,334 --> 00:04:34,461
You're the best.

97
00:04:35,442 --> 00:04:37,210
It's an honor.

98
00:04:37,210 --> 00:04:40,286
I've waited so long for this.

99
00:04:41,133 --> 00:04:42,843
Hello.

100
00:04:46,701 --> 00:04:48,951
Well... Aren't you guys

101
00:04:48,951 --> 00:04:51,458
actually pretty close?

102
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:53,400
No, that's rude.

103
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,361
It's been a while.

104
00:04:57,801 --> 00:04:59,167
Right.

105
00:04:59,167 --> 00:05:01,234
Great working with you.

106
00:05:02,868 --> 00:05:05,264
What a cold-blooded jerk.

107
00:05:05,264 --> 00:05:07,877
Come on, seriously,

108
00:05:07,877 --> 00:05:10,095
he's got zero feelings.

109
00:05:14,067 --> 00:05:16,516
This is driving me crazy.

110
00:05:18,567 --> 00:05:21,073
Hey, what are you doing?

111
00:05:21,073 --> 00:05:23,499
What? Why are you here?

112
00:05:23,499 --> 00:05:26,107
Why so shocked? We merged.

113
00:05:26,107 --> 00:05:29,387
I'm shocked you agreed to come.

114
00:05:30,041 --> 00:05:31,231
Am I in the right place?

115
00:05:31,231 --> 00:05:34,001
Spoiled then, spoiled now.

116
00:05:34,001 --> 00:05:36,428
Look around! This is PNJS!

117
00:05:36,428 --> 00:05:39,598
People would kill to get in here.

118
00:05:40,507 --> 00:05:43,307
Soo An, do you want to be a civil servant?

119
00:05:43,307 --> 00:05:46,567
Then why don't you even carry a pencil?

120
00:05:46,567 --> 00:05:50,016
You think you can beat kids
who study all day long?

121
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:53,090
So snap out of it and put in the work, okay?

122
00:05:53,090 --> 00:05:54,868
Come on, let's get to practice!

123
00:05:54,868 --> 00:05:56,230
Move it!

124
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:58,167
Being back at the agency,

125
00:05:58,167 --> 00:05:59,735
feels like home.

126
00:05:59,735 --> 00:06:01,516
Right, Jae Min?

127
00:06:02,901 --> 00:06:04,564
I...

128
00:06:05,667 --> 00:06:07,934
I'll be right back.

129
00:06:09,636 --> 00:06:11,504
Hey, where are you going?

130
00:06:17,603 --> 00:06:20,171
All right, come in.

131
00:06:26,050 --> 00:06:27,354
You're Jae Min?

132
00:06:27,354 --> 00:06:28,534
Yes,

133
00:06:28,534 --> 00:06:30,356
it's nice to see you.

134
00:06:31,133 --> 00:06:33,033
When you first signed,

135
00:06:33,033 --> 00:06:34,461
we met once, right?

136
00:06:34,461 --> 00:06:36,496
Yes, that's right.

137
00:06:42,267 --> 00:06:43,477
So,

138
00:06:43,477 --> 00:06:46,706
what brings you here?

139
00:06:46,706 --> 00:06:49,026
I honestly don't get it.

140
00:06:49,618 --> 00:06:52,746
After the survival show, nothing,

141
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:56,742
and now you're calling me back
as a debut trainee?

142
00:06:56,742 --> 00:06:59,352
I thought it was over.

143
00:07:01,221 --> 00:07:03,290
What are you saying, Jae Min?

144
00:07:03,290 --> 00:07:05,425
We're family.

145
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:08,534
I heard about that unfortunate business,

146
00:07:08,534 --> 00:07:10,634
but I was tied up with other things

147
00:07:10,634 --> 00:07:12,601
and couldn't look into it,

148
00:07:12,601 --> 00:07:16,669
and we all needed time to think.

149
00:07:18,234 --> 00:07:20,566
The agency needs you.

150
00:07:20,566 --> 00:07:22,943
Whatever you're worried about,

151
00:07:22,943 --> 00:07:25,237
we'll handle on our end,

152
00:07:25,237 --> 00:07:28,794
so take this shot and give it everything.

153
00:07:30,067 --> 00:07:33,185
I appreciate that, but...

154
00:07:35,934 --> 00:07:38,591
Oh, come on.

155
00:07:41,010 --> 00:07:42,817
Fine,

156
00:07:42,817 --> 00:07:44,864
if you don't want to,

157
00:07:44,864 --> 00:07:46,999
I can't force you.

158
00:07:58,878 --> 00:08:00,747
[Goo Sang Cheol]

159
00:08:00,747 --> 00:08:03,150
We respect your decision.

160
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:05,052
You're a grown adult now,

161
00:08:05,052 --> 00:08:06,652
aren't you?

162
00:08:09,255 --> 00:08:11,664
[The penalty for breach of contract
is 80 million won]

163
00:08:13,910 --> 00:08:17,364
[80 million won]
Just take responsibility,

164
00:08:17,364 --> 00:08:19,332
since you're an adult.

165
00:08:52,167 --> 00:08:54,533
Meet outside next time?

166
00:08:59,906 --> 00:09:02,171
[Show me more pretty spots in Korea]

167
00:09:05,745 --> 00:09:08,514
Let's meet at the school gate first.

168
00:09:12,634 --> 00:09:14,067
They said he's arrived.

169
00:09:14,067 --> 00:09:16,796
- Did you book the Thai place?
- Yes.

170
00:09:17,667 --> 00:09:19,259
Sawasdee krap.

171
00:09:19,259 --> 00:09:20,794
Sawasdee krap? Okay.

172
00:09:20,794 --> 00:09:22,828
Sawasdee krap.

173
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:50,234
- Sawasdee krap.
- Sawasdee krap.

174
00:09:50,234 --> 00:09:52,725
Nice to meet you.

175
00:09:52,725 --> 00:09:54,027
Is everything alright?

176
00:09:54,027 --> 00:09:55,097
Yes. It's nice.

177
00:09:55,097 --> 00:09:56,180
That sounds great.

178
00:09:56,180 --> 00:10:00,311
I'll show you to the CEO's office first.

179
00:10:02,402 --> 00:10:03,981
Why is he here?

180
00:10:03,981 --> 00:10:06,481
One, two, three, four,

181
00:10:06,481 --> 00:10:08,897
five, six, seven, eight.

182
00:10:08,897 --> 00:10:12,637
Five, six, seven, eight, one.

183
00:10:12,637 --> 00:10:13,713
Again.

184
00:10:13,713 --> 00:10:15,515
I'm checking in ten minutes,

185
00:10:15,515 --> 00:10:16,667
so keep practicing.

186
00:10:16,667 --> 00:10:18,505
- Yes.
- Yes.

187
00:10:22,021 --> 00:10:24,690
Two, three.

188
00:10:27,968 --> 00:10:29,334
Hey,

189
00:10:29,334 --> 00:10:31,598
I can't get this part,

190
00:10:31,598 --> 00:10:33,091
help me out.

191
00:10:33,091 --> 00:10:34,885
The wave should start from your chest,

192
00:10:34,885 --> 00:10:36,952
not like that, but like this.

193
00:10:36,952 --> 00:10:38,012
So how?

194
00:10:38,012 --> 00:10:39,139
Like this?

195
00:10:39,139 --> 00:10:40,406
Okay.

196
00:10:40,406 --> 00:10:42,775
One, two, three.

197
00:10:42,775 --> 00:10:44,300
Your leg.

198
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:46,378
A bit lower.

199
00:10:52,033 --> 00:10:53,501
- Hello.
- Hello.

200
00:10:53,501 --> 00:10:56,222
Hey, just relax.

201
00:10:58,133 --> 00:11:00,426
Come in.

202
00:11:11,713 --> 00:11:13,701
Everyone, say hello.

203
00:11:13,701 --> 00:11:15,717
So this guy right here,

204
00:11:15,717 --> 00:11:18,804
he's a huge name from Thailand,

205
00:11:18,804 --> 00:11:22,182
writing, composing, singing, he does it all,

206
00:11:22,182 --> 00:11:26,061
a genius musician, Khun.

207
00:11:26,061 --> 00:11:28,272
Introduce yourself?

208
00:11:28,272 --> 00:11:29,497
Nice to meet you.

209
00:11:29,497 --> 00:11:32,327
I'm looking forward to working with you guys.

210
00:11:33,767 --> 00:11:36,534
Anything is possible,
so let's just try everything.

211
00:11:36,534 --> 00:11:38,565
Okay.

212
00:11:38,565 --> 00:11:40,801
So what's the plan here?

213
00:11:40,801 --> 00:11:43,133
The debut team test is set for this week,

214
00:11:43,133 --> 00:11:45,200
and we're wrapping up basic lessons.

215
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,874
I see.

216
00:11:46,874 --> 00:11:48,501
All right.

217
00:11:48,501 --> 00:11:50,843
Want to grab dinner?

218
00:11:50,843 --> 00:11:52,208
Okay.

219
00:11:52,208 --> 00:11:53,979
Keep it up.

220
00:11:54,734 --> 00:11:56,949
- Take care.
- Take care.

221
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:01,839
What was that?

222
00:12:01,839 --> 00:12:04,663
Is he debuting with us?

223
00:12:05,267 --> 00:12:07,260
He wasn't introduced as a trainee.

224
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:09,567
He writes and composes,

225
00:12:09,567 --> 00:12:11,367
so maybe staff?

226
00:12:11,367 --> 00:12:12,608
Look at that face.

227
00:12:12,608 --> 00:12:14,087
Does he look like staff?

228
00:12:14,087 --> 00:12:17,070
Hyun Jae, heard anything?

229
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:18,780
I haven't heard a thing,

230
00:12:18,780 --> 00:12:20,866
but the CEO introduced someone himself...

231
00:12:20,866 --> 00:12:23,110
I think this is a first.

232
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:25,678
It's not common.

233
00:12:25,678 --> 00:12:28,290
So he's the debut team?

234
00:12:28,290 --> 00:12:29,461
Wait,

235
00:12:29,461 --> 00:12:32,210
so the debut team is already set?

236
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:34,004
Then what about us?

237
00:12:34,601 --> 00:12:36,256
Hyun Jae,

238
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:39,562
is the debut team already set?

239
00:12:39,562 --> 00:12:42,094
Not that I know of.

240
00:12:44,306 --> 00:12:47,467
So they're building the team around him.

241
00:12:47,467 --> 00:12:48,534
But he's foreign.

242
00:12:48,534 --> 00:12:51,688
Hey, that doesn't matter anymore.

243
00:12:51,688 --> 00:12:53,234
There's this T-culture thing,

244
00:12:53,234 --> 00:12:55,547
a huge market over there.

245
00:13:03,992 --> 00:13:05,477
Khun!

246
00:13:07,667 --> 00:13:09,822
I was shocked to see you walk in.

247
00:13:09,822 --> 00:13:12,100
I'm a trainee here.

248
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:15,227
Do you want to be an idol?

249
00:13:17,997 --> 00:13:19,732
Well...

250
00:13:21,868 --> 00:13:25,170
Anyway, good to see you here.

251
00:13:32,062 --> 00:13:33,596
Sorry.

252
00:13:33,596 --> 00:13:36,067
I was just shaking your hand.

253
00:13:36,067 --> 00:13:39,718
If you're going to grab my hand, ask first.

254
00:13:40,988 --> 00:13:43,210
You seem different.

255
00:13:47,027 --> 00:13:48,067
Because we're at work?

256
00:13:48,067 --> 00:13:49,929
No matter what, physical contact

257
00:13:49,929 --> 00:13:53,032
still needs consent, doesn't it?

258
00:13:55,402 --> 00:13:56,936
So...

259
00:13:56,936 --> 00:13:59,305
Is that what you planned from the start?

260
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:02,133
A plan?

261
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:03,233
What plan?

262
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:05,434
A plan to get

263
00:14:05,434 --> 00:14:07,279
close to me.

264
00:14:17,398 --> 00:14:18,609
This is so embarrassing.

265
00:14:18,609 --> 00:14:21,862
I've been waiting forever, so let's go.

266
00:14:21,862 --> 00:14:24,565
He's not a puppy,
so why is he trailing him around?

267
00:14:24,565 --> 00:14:25,782
Honestly, for the test,

268
00:14:25,782 --> 00:14:27,659
shouldn't we pair with people we click with?

269
00:14:27,659 --> 00:14:30,996
Yoon Soo An, partner with me.

270
00:14:30,996 --> 00:14:33,100
That way the rest will mix too.

271
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:34,467
I never said that.

272
00:14:34,467 --> 00:14:36,634
Don't you talk like that.

273
00:14:36,634 --> 00:14:38,470
So from now on,

274
00:14:39,334 --> 00:14:42,007
how should we handle this?

275
00:14:42,007 --> 00:14:44,051
Excuse me.

276
00:14:44,051 --> 00:14:45,690
Are you...
